MEGAN PETE - using her real name because she’s a real human being not a prop or a stallion, she’s a black woman who was assaulted by a man. After hearing the 911 call and the jail call, my heart further bleeds for this woman.  Imagine being shot multiple times and then protecting the shooter by lying for him (the logic behind that alone is mind blowing to me). The amount of trauma and damage she’s faced through the assault, judgment and callousness by her own people is sad.  The amount of black women & men who didn’t & still don’t  believe her is sickening. Yes - there are inconsistencies, which is normal cuz clearly Kylie got everyone blackout drunk upon entering her home that night. I Guarantee you this, if this had happen to KYLIE that night she wouldn’t have to convince anyone she was shot and by who? Never!! Megan will have a long road to becoming healthy and whole again. However, One things clear to me, God has his hand over her life because I don’t know many HUMANS who can navigate some of what she’s been through in her life and still crack a smile. “Protect Black Women” has become a popular hashtag in our community, but we have to actually do the work for it to matter!  #GOD #ProtectBlackWomen #IStandWithMegan #StopAssaultPeriod
You gotta admit, Malik is really trying! This man is taking his therapy very seriously and I for one am proud! 😂 #TheGame 🏈 #RunningMyRace #MailkEldebargeWright

Early on We called ourselves “the little engine that could” and almost 20th later…WE DID!! 🏈

2022 wasn’t an easy one for me, no matter how successful it was in some ways, in other ways I’ve endured more than I’m willing to share, but then again we all have. We play on this app and we see other people manufactured lives, smiles & happiness, but if you really pay attention humanity as a whole is suffering, it’s right in your face. However, I believe GOD uses everything we endure for the greater good of us all.  I hope this year is kind to you, and YOU are kind to YOU. I hope you experience love that’s unconditional, peace that’s unshakable, joy that’s unbreakable, and that GOD shows you a miracle that’s unbelievable! God I ask you to show up for us and show out, blow our minds with your goodness and grace in 2023 father! Heal those who need it, cast your light into the darkest spots in our heart & spirits and break the chains of bondage. My brothers & Sisters - Prayer & Meditation will change your life, and your families lives as well. In 2023, I pray for healing, for unconditional love, for a whole and healthy mind body and spirit. In 2023, kindness, empathy & compassion, are absolutely free! 
I love you all, Happy New Year world 🌎

Circa 2005 I’d auditioned for Derwin 4Xs & tested with the network 2X and there was no 5th audition. I wasn’t the guy for the part.  A week later id gotten a call from the casting director (Susan) personally, she said the producers want to see you for another role, the role of MALIK. At that time I was drained, I said no thank you, I was still so raw from the process & the rejection.  GOD told me in a dream that HE decides when the door is closed but if I don’t show up for my DREAM it will always be just that, a dream. So I went and I didn’t think I was Malik, but this lovely woman on my lap @maraakil saw something in me that I didn’t see. She saw MALIK in me, and so did her husband #SALIM. I’ll never forget Salim pulls me aside after a  work session, I was going back and forth in the character #Malik (keep in mind, I was still attached to Derwin) so I was playing Malik two sided. I was so connected to the GOD in Derwin I was giving Malik too much sensitivity, I couldn’t let Derwin go, it was too soon, It was a lot on me. Salim saw this battle in me, he pulled me aside again (like the loving & sensitive man he is) & told me to go back in there, follow my heart and “don’t you change a motherfucking thing” 🤣 so I took his LEADERSHIP & DIRECTION, went back in and didn’t change a damn thing, booked the role and the rest is History.  I never could have chosen this path for myself, but this has been the biggest reward of my career. Back then, we were all in fear of being type casted & look at me now, almost 20 years later in the same character, living in the biggest BLESSING of my career. Had @maraakil & Salim not seen me beyond me, I don’t know what career path I would have chosen for myself or if I would still be an ACTOR - Director at all.  I know everyone in this photo has moved on but almost 20yrs later, I still LOVE each one of them with all my heart and soul. Shows are a complexed mosaic of artist and sometimes, most times OUR paths change direction but for me, when I LOVE you it’s hard to STOP, especially when I know how hard GOD worked to bring US all together.  #TheGameOGs #OriginStories #ReunionOneDay #DirectedByMe 🤯 #ThankYouFans! #BoomBoomClap 🏈

For Context - I’m a little Black Boy from Montgomery Al, population of about 198,665 -  I dropped out of high school after loosing my Grandmother - This was devastating for me & my family because She was OUR rock. After her passing, all I had left was a Dream and a personal relationship with GOD, There was no road map or blueprint for us #Dreamers in Alabama - Bottom line is Keep going, keep Growing 🌎 be kind, work hard & don’t give up! When GOD opens the doors, pathways, hallways & windows to your life, no man can close them. Embrace YOUR Race & We will get there one small victory lap at a time. Thank you #GameFam for your kind & loving words on the experience we shared -  I love and  respect each of you to infinity and Beyond ✨ #KeepGoing #GOD #Dreamers #Bama #theGameOvertime #RunningMyRace #Humble #ThankYouFans!

BLACK MEN (We- Me-You) are in national crisis and instead of talking about it, I’ve decided to do something about it. December, 2022 • I fulfilled a new dream of mine. I Created, Executive Produced, Hosted & Co Directed a talk show entitled (THE GOOD FELLAS) @TheGoodFellasTalk with some of the most dynamic #BlackMEN I’ve met on my life’s journey. A show created by #BlackMEN for everyone. A show that is a safe space for all #BlackMEN to be Our most authentic selves without any restrictions or repercussions or judgement, from anyone! A show that will change the lives of my brothers world wide. A show that will free #BlackMEN & #BlackBOYS far beyond our physical, mental, emotional and spiritual boundaries. A show that will heal and expand the knowledge we once believed to be our limited truth. A show that all #WOMEN  need to see to aide in understanding the importance of #BlackMEN having a safe space, to heal, learn and grow from one another. In an effort to be of service to ourselves, our partners, our mothers, our families and our #Children. This show is tilted THE GOOD FELLAS - because we aim to dismantle the myth that #BlackMEN are a threat to Humanity, to society, to our homes, to our children, to our communities and to OURSELVES! 
Brothers & Sisters - GOOD FELLAS will change OUR lives as we know it. #CommingSoon #GOODFELLAS #BlackHistory

🎈September 12th - with my age has come wisdom. The vision and understanding that all life is a gift. Every second, every breath bares a weight of enlightenment, if you’re 👁️ is open. I see things clearer now than ever before, that’s wisdom. God has guided me to my path of peace, my path of wholeness, my path of fortune, therefore I’ve said goodbye to some things, with love & appreciation for their lessons within my journey. But more importantly, I’ve said HELLO to the presence of ME fully, finally - wassup Hosea! I look forward to my NOW & my future without mourning my past, That’s peace. Peace that passes all understanding, that’s GOD.  I’m thankful I’m still here, and thriving, no longer surviving, accepting all things and humans aren’t for me, some have seasons, most have  reasons, but all of it works for the greater good of your journey, if you believe.  Thank you GOD for another wonderful & challenging year, I AM forever grateful you allowed me to live a life fully actualized & realized. HBD to the little black boy from Montgomery Alabama who was brave enough to live HIS life fully & wholeheartedly while spreading love and kindness to many people along the way.  September 12th 🎂
